# Create a New Proposal

You're starting a new change proposal. Follow these steps to create one.

## Step 1: Choose a Module

Changes should belong to a module (an epic grouping related work).

{%- if modules and modules|length > 0 %}
### Available Modules

| ID | Name |
|----|------|
{%- for m in modules %}
| {{ m.id }} | {{ m.name }} |
{%- endfor %}

Choose an existing module if your change fits its scope, or create a new one.
{%- else %}
No modules exist yet. You can:
- Use module `000` for standalone/ungrouped changes
- Create a new module with `spool create module <name>`
{%- endif %}

## Step 2: Create the Change

```bash
spool create change "<change-name>" --module <module-id>
```

**Naming conventions:**
- Use kebab-case: `add-user-auth`, `fix-login-bug`
- Prefer verb-led names: `add-`, `update-`, `remove-`, `refactor-`
- Keep it short and descriptive

**Example:**
```bash
spool create change "add-two-factor-auth" --module 001
# Creates: .spool/changes/001-05_add-two-factor-auth/
```

## Step 3: Get Proposal Instructions

After creating the change, get detailed instructions:

```bash
spool agent instruction proposal --change <change-id>
```

This will provide:
- Template for `proposal.md`
- Guidelines for spec deltas
- Validation requirements

## Step 4: Write the Proposal

Your change directory will contain:
```
.spool/changes/<change-id>/
├── proposal.md     # Why and what (create this)
├── tasks.md        # Implementation steps (create this)
├── design.md       # Technical decisions (optional)
└── specs/          # Delta changes to specifications
    └── <capability>/
        └── spec.md # ADDED/MODIFIED/REMOVED requirements
```

### proposal.md Template

```markdown
## Why

<!-- 1-2 sentences on the problem or opportunity -->

## What Changes

<!-- Bullet list of changes. Mark breaking changes with **BREAKING** -->

## Capabilities

### New Capabilities

<!-- Each creates specs/<name>/spec.md -->
- `<name>`: <brief description>

### Modified Capabilities

<!-- Existing capabilities whose requirements are changing -->

## Impact

<!-- Affected code, APIs, dependencies -->
```

## Step 5: Validate

```bash
spool validate <change-id> --strict
```

Fix any errors before proceeding.

